dmca.title: Notice of Copyright Infringement/DMCA Take Down Demand per 17 USC 512 (c)

-----Original Message-----
From: Justin Schlecter [mailto:justin@upsideout.com] 
Sent: Monday, February 12, 2007 2:12 AM
To: DMCA
Subject: Notice of Copyright Infringement/DMCA Take Down Demand per 17
USC 512 (c)

Attention: Legal Department

Dear Sir or Madam,

I am writing to file a notice of copyright infringement in accordance  
with the Digital Millennium Copyright Act.

1. The copyrighted work at issue is the text that appears on "http:// 
urlencoded.com/". URLEncoded.com is a wholly owned subsidiary of  
UpsideOut, Inc.

2. The material that we believe is infringing the copyrighted work  
listed in item #1 appears on "http://123proxy.net/download/ 
anonyproxy.rar" which is located at IP address "74.52.236.194".  
Specifically, the material is, "Unlisted IP Address
Prevent tracking of your internet access by the Web sites you view,  
hackers and others.

URL Encoded
Scrambles web page URLs, preventing ISPs from tracking or logging  
your surfing.

Safe Cookies
Filters cookies into temporary, session-only activity.

Script Blocking
Prevents potentially harmful Java, JavaScript, ActiveX and other code  
from violating your privacy.

Ad Filtering
Prevents most popup windows and banner ads from appearing.

Referrer Blocking
Shields previously-viewed Web pages from outside parties.

Hide Page Titles
Prevents page titles from appearing in the browsers history file.

Text Data Only
Traffic restricted to text data only, makes browsing fastest.

Minimize Caching
Prevent any caching of anything retrieved through the proxy.

OS & Browser Shielding
Prevents visited sites and other parties from detecting your OS and  
browser type.

Web Bug Blocking
Blocks one-pixel gifs commonly used for Web tracking.

100% Free
Best fo all it's completely free. No forced banners. No limit to the  
number of websites you can access.
". This material is copied in it's entirety.
